# Contact form delivery (Web3Forms — https://web3forms.com)
#
# The form submits directly from the browser (Web3Forms' free plan blocks
# server-side requests), so the access key MUST use the NEXT_PUBLIC_ prefix
# to be readable client-side. The Web3Forms access key is public by design.
#
# 1. Sign up at web3forms.com using ashishadhikari481@gmail.com
#    (messages are delivered to the inbox the key is registered under).
# 2. Copy your Access Key below.
# 3. Local dev: copy this file to `.env.local` and fill in the value.
#    Production: add NEXT_PUBLIC_WEB3FORMS_ACCESS_KEY in Netlify
#    (Site configuration → Environment variables), then redeploy — NEXT_PUBLIC_
#    vars are baked in at build time, so a rebuild is required after changing it.
NEXT_PUBLIC_WEB3FORMS_ACCESS_KEY=your-web3forms-access-key
